  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Architectural Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities :</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Collaborate with architects, engineers, and consultants to ensure the integration of design elements across disciplines</li>\n  <li>Review and coordinate architectural plans, drawings and specifications to maintain design intent and accuracy</li>\n  <li>Assist in the planning, scheduling, and management of architectural projects</li>\n  <li>Monitor project progress, ensuring timelines and budgets are adhered to</li>\n  <li>Prepare, review, and manage architectural documentation, including design proposals, tender packages and construction documents</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements :</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or Degree in Building/Architecture or other related field</li>\n  <li>Minimum 3–5 years of experience in architectural design, project coordination, or related roles</li>\n  <li>Proficient in architectural software such as AutoCAD, Revit, SketchUp, and BIM tools</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of construction techniques, building codes and standards</li>\n  <li>Good technical detailing , specification knowledge and aesthetic sensibilities</li>\n  <li>Problem-solving mindset with attention to detail</li>\n  <li>Proactive, self-motivated and adaptable to dynamic project requirements</li>\n</ul>",
